# Development Workflow

## Getting Started

1. Install dependencies: `npm install`
2. Run development server: `npm run dev`

## Project Commands

- [package.json](mdc:package.json): Contains project scripts
  - `npm run dev`: Start development server
  - `npm run build`: Build for production
  - `npm run build:win`: Build for Windows

## Project Structure

The project follows a typical Nextron structure:

- Frontend code lives in the [renderer/](mdc:renderer) directory
- Electron code lives in the [main/](mdc:main) directory
- Build output goes to the [dist/](mdc:dist) directory

## Window Creation

- [main/helpers/create-window.ts](mdc:main/helpers/create-window.ts): Helper for creating application windows
